result.execSummary:
The defendant Leslie M Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Leslie M Taylor in court with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty. Cts. 1 and 3 dismissed and read-in. Defense advises they are willing to accept the restitution and are not disputing the amount. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 2:
- Total sentence: 2 years (Initial Confinement: 1 year - 1 day credit, Extended Supervision: 1 year)  Stayed for 2 years Probation - may be transferred to Tennessee under the Interstate Compact transfer
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- Restitution of $1026.00 - $150.00 to be paid to Waukesha Police Department Metro and $876.00 to be paid to Steve B. to be paid as a Condition of Probation.
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Conditions of  Probation:   Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No drug paraphernalia. Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions. Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling. No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed. Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided
 - Defendant to perform 100 hours of community service as a Condition of Probation.
